data.title: Vál, Fejér, Hungary
data.text:
Vál, a charming town in Fejér County, Hungary, is situated at coordinates 47.3626400 latitude and 18.6793100 longitude. With a temperate climate, Vál experiences warm summers and cool winters. Its rich history dates back to the 13th century, and its heritage is evident in its well-preserved architectural landmarks, including the medieval church and the Baroque-style town hall.
